TestLink 1.6.Beta - ReadMe

1. Introduction
===============================================================

    TestLink is a web based test management and test execution system.
    It enables quality assurance teams to create and manage their test cases
    as well as to organize them into test plans. These test plans allow team
    members to execute test cases and track test results dynamically.
    
    TestLink is a GPL licensed open source project. 
    All of the source code behind TestLink is freely available
    for download via SourceForge at http://www.sourceforge.net.If you are 
    interested in contributing to the TestLink effort feel free to contact us.

2. Installation and System Requirements
===============================================================
 
   TestLink environment includes PHP4, MySQL and a Web-server (e.g.  functional 
   EasyPHP, WAMP installation).
   
   Download: You can get the newest version at sourceforge.net at 
   https://sourceforge.net/projects/testlink/.
    
   Installation and configuration is described in directory
   <testlink_root>/documentation/installation-manual.html or Installation and
   Configuration manual at http://testlink.sourceforge.net/docs/docs/toc.php.
   
   Update from previous versions of TestLink : Database schema was
   changed. We recommend to use installation script.

3. Release notes TestLink 1.6.RC1
===============================================================
 
    This release is a candidate to release for TestLink 1.6.0. The development 
    of this version is stoped now. Only bug fixing will be applied
    until official release. See CHANGELOG for more information about new
    features, bug fixes and changes.

4. Known problems
===============================================================

    There are known issues:
      
        No blocking issue is known at the time.
      
        Several minor issues are listed in TestLink Bug Tracking System.
      
        Documentation is still as draft.
    

5. Bug Reports and Feedback
===============================================================

   The Bug Overview on the TestLink web site lets you search for and
    examine existing bug reports, submit your own bug reports, and tell us
    which bug fixes matter most to you. To submit a bug or a feature, please use 
    our  Mantis installation at http://www.testlink.org/mantis/ for TestLink. 
    
    You can see ther also the current bugs and requests.You may also contact 
    us at the TestLink forum at http://www.testlink.org/tiki/tiki-forums.php.
    
    